Learning **Pandas** is essential for data manipulation and analysis in Python. 
Below is a comprehensive list of **resources** to help you master Pandas, ranging from beginner to advanced levels.

---

## **1. Official Documentation**
- **Pandas Documentation**:  
  The official documentation is the most reliable and detailed resource.  
  ðŸ”— [https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/](https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/)

---

## **2. Free Online Tutorials and Courses**
### **Beginner-Friendly Tutorials**
- **W3Schools Pandas Tutorial**:  
  A simple and interactive tutorial for beginners.  
  ðŸ”— [https://www.w3schools.com/python/pandas/](https://www.w3schools.com/python/pandas/)

- **Real Python Pandas Tutorials**:  
  A collection of beginner-friendly tutorials with examples.  
  ðŸ”— [https://realpython.com/tutorials/pandas/](https://realpython.com/tutorials/pandas/)

- **Kaggle Learn: Pandas**:  
  A hands-on course with exercises and datasets.  
  ðŸ”— [https://www.kaggle.com/learn/pandas](https://www.kaggle.com/learn/pandas)

### **Intermediate to Advanced Tutorials**
- **DataCamp Pandas Courses**:  
  Interactive courses with exercises (free and paid options available).  
  ðŸ”— [https://www.datacamp.com/courses/pandas-foundations](https://www.datacamp.com/courses/pandas-foundations)

- **Google's Python Pandas Tutorial**:  
  A free tutorial from Google for data analysis with Pandas.  
  ðŸ”— [https://developers.google.com/edu/python/pandas](https://developers.google.com/edu/python/pandas)

