## **3. Books**
### **For Beginners**
- **"Python for Data Analysis" by Wes McKinney**:  
  Written by the creator of Pandas, this book is a must-read for beginners.  
  ðŸ”— [Amazon Link](https://www.amazon.com/Python-Data-Analysis-Wrangling-IPython/dp/1491957662)

- **"Pandas Cookbook" by Theodore Petrou**:  
  A practical guide with recipes for solving real-world data problems.  
  ðŸ”— [Amazon Link](https://www.amazon.com/Pandas-Cookbook-Recipes-Scientific-Computing/dp/1784393878)

### **For Advanced Users**
- **"Mastering Pandas" by Ashish Kumar**:  
  Focuses on advanced techniques and performance optimization.  
  ðŸ”— [Amazon Link](https://www.amazon.com/Mastering-Pandas-Ashish-Kumar/dp/1789343235)

